    "body": "<div class=\"stimulus_reference \" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p1\"><p class=\"standalone_statement style:1 \"><span class=\"math_expression \"><span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"negative x plus y, equals negative 3 point 5, and, x plus 3 y, equals 9 point 5\"></span></span></p></div>\n",
    "prompt": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph \">If <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the ordered pair x comma y\"></span> satisfies the system of equations above, what is the value of <span class=\"italic\">y</span> ?</p>\n",
    "answer": {
      "style": "SPR",
      "rationale": "<p>The correct answer is <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"three halves\"></span>. One method for solving the system of equations for <span class=\"italic\">y</span> is to add corresponding sides of the two equations. Adding the left-hand sides gives <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"open parenthesis, negative x plus y, close parenthesis, plus, open parenthesis, x plus 3 y, close parenthesis\"></span>, or 4<span class=\"italic\">y</span>. Adding the right-hand sides yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"negative 3 point 5 plus 9 point 5, equals 6\"></span>. It follows that <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"4 y equals 6\"></span>. Finally, dividing both sides of <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"4 y equals 6\"></span> by 4 yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"y equals six fourths\"></span> or <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"three halves\"></span>. Note that 3/2 and 1.5 are examples of ways to enter a correct answer.<div data-ae_invis=\"true\" id=\"level-access-access-assistant-highlight-container\">&nbsp;</div></p>\n"
    }
